transcript.speaker: Interviewer
transcript.text: Hello, thank you for participating in this interview. I'm going to ask you some questions about your health and experiences. Let's begin.

transcript.speaker: Interviewer
transcript.text: Can you tell me a bit about yourself and your current life situation?

Sure! My name is Emma, and I'm 26 years old. I live in a small rural area in North Dakota. I work as a cashier, which keeps me busy, but I find that I don't get a lot of exercise. I graduated from high school, but I haven't pursued any further education. I'm single and living on a lower-middle income, and I have Medicaid for my health insurance. 

In terms of my health, I’ve had a few issues lately. I deal with gingivitis and have had some tooth infections. I also had viral sinusitis a while back, which wasn't fun at all. I don’t usually go to the doctor unless I really need to, mainly because of the limited healthcare access in my area. I know I have a medication review due, but I haven't been able to schedule an appointment yet. I occasionally smoke, which I know isn’t the best for my health. Overall, I’m just trying to manage things as best as I can. 

Does that give you a good picture of my current situation?
